13:47.741 --> 13:50.343
Jenna's turned into a
real "Jizzed-on Jane."

13:50.411 --> 13:51.812
You really want to come with me?

13:51.879 --> 13:53.814
You're my best friend, Ryan.

13:53.881 --> 13:55.481
I love you.

13:55.549 --> 13:57.550
Of course I want to come.

14:00.721 --> 14:02.956
(exhales)

14:04.758 --> 14:07.093
What is that?

14:07.161 --> 14:09.129
I know that smell.

14:09.197 --> 14:11.832
Uh, it's probably my ChapStick.

14:15.303 --> 14:16.703
It was you.

14:16.770 --> 14:18.338
Now, hold on, Wilfred.

14:18.405 --> 14:20.273
It-it's complicated.
(knocking)

14:20.341 --> 14:22.142
Your face

14:22.210 --> 14:24.477
is the saddle Jenna's
been giddyupping on?

14:24.545 --> 14:26.146
No, no, no, no, no!
It was only one kiss.

14:26.147 --> 14:28.315
(shouts) Wilfred, stop!

14:28.382 --> 14:31.451
I'll eat your genitalia, bitch!
HENRY: Ryan?

14:31.518 --> 14:34.020
(Wilfred grunting)
HENRY: Ryan?

14:34.088 --> 14:35.922
Ryan!
WILFRED: You were supposed

14:35.990 --> 14:37.690
to be my best friend!

14:37.758 --> 14:39.192
I-I am!

14:39.260 --> 14:41.127
I didn't plan on it!
She kissed me!

14:41.195 --> 14:42.729
Besides, it's-it's over now!

14:42.796 --> 14:44.064
Oh, God. This is worse
than I thought.

14:44.131 --> 14:45.698
I'm taking you to get some help.

14:45.766 --> 14:48.301
Let go, Wilfred!
(Wilfred grunting)

14:48.369 --> 14:50.503
Let go! Bad dog!
Stay away from me!

14:50.571 --> 14:52.272
You've got nothing
to do with this!

14:52.340 --> 14:53.706
Ryan, you're not well.

14:53.774 --> 14:54.841
You have to... Whoa!

14:57.111 --> 14:59.045
Dad?

15:04.404 --> 15:06.405
(church bell ringing)

15:06.472 --> 15:07.631
Thanks for coming.

15:07.751 --> 15:10.776
I appreciate it.
Of course, Ryan.

15:12.312 --> 15:14.036
I'm sorry we can't stay long.

15:14.156 --> 15:16.648
We've got Wilfred in the car.

15:16.716 --> 15:18.817
I understand.

15:26.839 --> 15:28.794
I feel horrible
about this, mate.

15:28.861 --> 15:30.222
You don't have
to keep apologizing.

15:30.252 --> 15:31.820
It was a total accident.

15:31.887 --> 15:33.888
I only left my tennis ball there
in the hopes

15:33.956 --> 15:35.890
that someone would, like,
kick it down the stairs

15:35.958 --> 15:38.626
and I'd chase it down
and bring it back up to them

15:38.694 --> 15:40.195
and then repeat that, like,

15:40.262 --> 15:41.696
7,000 times in a row.

15:41.764 --> 15:43.031
I know.
It's okay, Wilfred.

15:43.099 --> 15:44.398
I'm willing to forget

15:44.466 --> 15:46.201
about you and Jenna.

15:46.268 --> 15:48.436
We've just got to put a stop
to all this fighting

15:48.503 --> 15:50.071
before someone gets hurt.

15:50.139 --> 15:51.806
You know what I mean.

15:51.874 --> 15:54.408
If it's any consolation,

15:54.476 --> 15:58.246
now that your dad's...
you know... you can

15:58.313 --> 16:01.082
finally feel free,
live your own life.

16:01.150 --> 16:03.351
Also,

16:03.418 --> 16:06.821
it's probably not the right time
to bring it up, but this...

16:06.889 --> 16:09.457
this is how you crack a window.

16:09.524 --> 16:10.591
Yep.

16:15.297 --> 16:17.632
Sorry for your loss, Ryan.

16:17.699 --> 16:20.501
Hank was always
so proud of you.

16:20.569 --> 16:22.904
I want you to know that even
with your father's passing,

16:22.972 --> 16:25.506
we'd still love for you to
oversee the pro bono division.

16:25.574 --> 16:27.776
Pro bono division?

16:27.843 --> 16:30.211
Uh, can't say I'm the biggest
supporter of the idea,

16:30.279 --> 16:32.981
but we've already found several
cases related to prisoners

16:33.048 --> 16:34.883
with mental health issues.

16:34.950 --> 16:38.119
Your father was
very specific about that.

16:41.757 --> 16:44.959
Do you think he was only
just trying to help us?

16:46.561 --> 16:49.497
When your dad had me committed,

16:49.564 --> 16:52.366
I know it crushed him.

16:52.434 --> 16:55.870
He was scared that you would
turn out the same way.

16:55.938 --> 17:00.608
So... he made you
into a little lawyer, which...

17:00.676 --> 17:03.711
must have given you
some kind of structure.

17:05.915 --> 17:09.250
You know, I don't think
I could've admitted this

17:09.318 --> 17:11.185
while he was
still alive, but...

17:11.252 --> 17:13.688
yeah, maybe, I think...

17:13.755 --> 17:17.692
he was actually
trying to help us.

17:17.759 --> 17:21.561
In his own dysfunctional,
dickheadish way.

17:29.538 --> 17:31.005
Hey, can you do me a tiny favor

17:31.073 --> 17:32.707
and smash this bit
of glass down here?

17:32.774 --> 17:35.076
You've always been against me
reconciling with my father.

17:35.144 --> 17:36.677
Since the day we met.
Look,

17:36.745 --> 17:38.346
as interesting as all this is,
I really need to...

17:38.413 --> 17:40.849
Oh, there we go. And I'm peeing.

17:40.916 --> 17:43.384
This past week,
I've been fighting so hard

17:43.452 --> 17:45.286
to save our friendship

17:45.354 --> 17:47.055
instead of focusing
on the relationship

17:47.122 --> 17:49.423
that actually mattered:
the one with my father.

17:49.491 --> 17:50.892
Ryan, what are you saying?

17:50.960 --> 17:53.361
I'm not well when I'm with you.

17:53.428 --> 17:55.763
I am so sick
of seeing everything

17:55.831 --> 17:57.598
through Wilfred-tinted lenses.

17:57.666 --> 17:58.532
Ryan...

